article.headline: Utah 62, TCU 54
article.story: FORT WORTH, Texas -- Carlon Brown scored 14 points and had 12 rebounds to help lead Utah to a 62-54 victory over TCU on Wednesday night. Luke Nevill added 12 points and Lawrence Borha added 11 for Utah (15-7, 6-2 Mountain West). Kevin Langford led TCU (13-9, 4-4) with 22 points and Ronnie Moss added 14. Utah took its first lead of the game with 13:19 to go in the second half on a jumper by Nevill for a 40-39 lead. The Utes led the rest of the way, by as much as eight points. TCU's Zvonko Buljan cut the lead to 57-54 with a couple of free throws with 2:18 left, but Nevill and Luka Drca hit six free throws the rest of the way for the final margin. TCU led 32-27 at the half.
